    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.1",
      "en": "Discover the advanced technology stack and innovative architecture that powers Elemento's cutting-edge cloud solutions.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.10",
      "en": "Desktop and mobile documentation for deploying, managing, using, and retiring VMs consistently across providers.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.11",
      "en": "Formal write-up on cloud service composition with the C4 protocol and the connector specification your integrations can target.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.12",
      "en": "How we translate existing cloud provider APIs into the shapes Elemento expects, so integrations stay maintainable.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.13",
      "en": "Command-line workflows for installing, configuring, and operating AtomOS alongside guided setup and private-cloud demos.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.14",
      "en": "Built with modern, proven technologies for reliability, performance, and sustainability",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.15",
      "en": "Our patented C4 Protocol (patented in Italy, patent pending worldwide) is a standardized protocol that enables cloud service providers to integrate seamlessly with enterprise-grade multi-cloud management platforms. This revolutionary technology simplifies cloud provider integration and expands market reach. The Elemento Cloud Network book on BookStack hosts the C4 whitepaper, connector specification, and Meson tech pack for mapping existing provider APIs into C4-shaped services. Learn about our product ecosystem and technical insights .",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.16",
      "en": "Patented technology enabling standardized multi-cloud integration and resource management across any cloud provider.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.17",
      "en": "How the core layers of Elemento work together",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.18",
      "en": "The central management layer that orchestrates all platform operations, including Kubernetes control plane, API gateway, and management interfaces. Documentation describes this as the Elemento Cloud Network gateway that links existing clouds into a single operational model.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.19",
      "en": "The execution layer where your applications run, including compute resources, storage systems, and networking components.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.2",
      "en": "A technology-first approach to multi-cloud freedom",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.20",
      "en": "User interfaces, APIs, and automation tools that provide access to platform capabilities and enable infrastructure as code. Electros covers desktop and mobile control planes for the full VM lifecycle on any cloud, while Nucleus documents the CLI for installing and operating AtomOS—both are indexed on BookStack .",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.21",
      "en": "Comprehensive monitoring, logging, and analytics that provide insights into performance, costs, and environmental impact. Learn about our monitoring solutions and support services .",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.22",
      "en": "Modern and proven technologies powering our cloud-native platform",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.23",
      "en": "Docker containers with Kubernetes orchestration for consistent deployment and scaling across any environment. AtomOS is our Linux KVM-based hypervisor; the wiki publishes ESXi-oriented comparison tables , guest OS notes, and filesystem versus disk-image guidance.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.24",
      "en": "Terraform, Ansible and Pulumi integration for automated infrastructure management and deployment.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.25",
      "en": "Prometheus, Grafana, and ELK stack for comprehensive monitoring, logging, and alerting.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.26",
      "en": "Built-in security scanning, compliance frameworks, and enterprise-grade encryption.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.27",
      "en": "Advanced networking with load balancing, service mesh, and global traffic management.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.28",
      "en": "Distributed storage systems with automatic backup, replication, and disaster recovery.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.29",
      "en": "Uptime",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.3",
      "en": "Elemento empowers organizations to manage complex IT infrastructures across multiple clouds and on-premises environments seamlessly.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.30",
      "en": "Average Latency",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.31",
      "en": "Energy Savings",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.32",
      "en": "Datacenters Connected",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.33",
      "en": "Technology with sustainability at its core.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.34",
      "en": "Optimize resource allocation based on energy efficiency and carbon impact.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.35",
      "en": "Track energy usage and CO₂ emissions across providers.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.36",
      "en": "Partnering with renewable-powered data centers worldwide.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.37",
      "en": "Analytics and reporting to meet ESG and compliance goals.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.38",
      "en": "Continuously evolving to stay ahead of enterprise needs",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.39",
      "en": "Machine learning algorithms that automatically optimize resource allocation, cost management, and performance tuning.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.4",
      "en": "Our architecture integrates the C4 Protocol for standardized multi-cloud connectivity, Kubernetes for container orchestration, and Infrastructure as Code to automate deployments. For architecture diagrams, install guides, and protocol detail, see our technical documentation on BookStack . Explore our product implementations and learn about our company vision .",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.40",
      "en": "Advanced algorithms that consider carbon intensity when making workload placement decisions.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.41",
      "en": "Collaborating with leading universities and research institutions to advance cloud computing technology.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.42",
      "en": "Extending our platform to edge locations for low-latency applications and IoT deployments.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.43",
      "en": "Implementing advanced security models that verify every request and connection.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.44",
      "en": "Explore our comprehensive suite of cloud infrastructure products",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.45",
      "en": "Advanced container orchestration platform built on Kubernetes for seamless deployment and management of containerized applications.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.46",
      "en": "Intelligent infrastructure automation platform that simplifies deployment and management of cloud resources across multiple providers.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.47",
      "en": "Advanced networking platform providing global connectivity, intelligent load balancing, and seamless traffic management.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.48",
      "en": "Ready to see how our cutting-edge technology can transform your infrastructure? Learn about our company background and explore our product offerings .",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.5",
      "en": "With a cloud-agnostic and infrastructure-neutral design, Elemento ensures businesses can scale , adapt , and innovate without vendor lock-in.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.6",
      "en": "Structured guides and specs on our BookStack wiki",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.7",
      "en": "The same material we use for onboarding and integration lives in one place: starter packs, C4 whitepapers and protocol specs, AtomOS and Nucleus CLI install guides, Electros tech notes, comparison tables against legacy hypervisors, and reference architecture. Follow the links below to read the full chapters.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.8",
      "en": "API gateway patterns that connect existing clouds, plus starter content that ties together C4, installs, and deeper technical packs.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "body.technology.p.9",
      "en": "Feature-by-feature views of our Linux KVM-based hypervisor versus VMware ESXi, with guest OS coverage and filesystem versus disk-image compatibility matrices.",
      "it": "",
      "source": "technology.html",
      "context": "<p>"
    },
